('Lead Test Developer ','9','Lead Test Developer ','Will architect plans for automated and non automated test scripts of applications and systems based on functional and technical specifications as provided by the CRMAS team.  ','Must possess a Masters degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Management Information Systems, or a closely related field, plus 1 year of experience in the job offered or in designing and developing test plans, test suits, and automated scripts.','SC','',''),
('Financial Reporting Specialist I','10',' The position is responsible for the assembly and review or quarterly and annual reports to stockholders of AgFirst, 23 Associations and the District.  All reports and disclosures are completed in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States and FCA regulations, as well as requirement set forth by the Funding Corporation.  Requires a balanced combination of technical and software knowledge, along with extensive computer and customer service skills.','','Responsibilities: Assembly of internal management reports and financial information, including the monthly Board reports.  Provide expertise required to layout and properly format quarterly and annual reports.  Requirements:  Accounting or related degree.  Exposure to serving customers at a high level in a multi-location environment.  Expert level of knowledge of word processing, desktop publishing and financial spreadsheet programs.  Four or more years of related or similar work experience, with high level of skills proficiency.  Strong analytical skills, ability to work independently with minimal instruction, ability to set priorities and meet deadlines.  Strong oral and written communication skills. Grade and Salary commensurate upon experience. EEO.','SC','',''),
('Lead System Administrator',' 13','This position provides technical support for the corporate server infrastructure for specific development and maintenance.Responsibilities includeinstallation, configuration of server components, and providing problem diagnosis/resolutions for clients/servers to assure timely and efficient delivery of system services. Lead Citrix administrator responsible for the design and functionality of the Citrix environments. Serves as lead/team member on assigned network related projects. Ensures best practices are designed, implemented and enforces. Occasional travel required.','','Responsibilities: Serve as technical lead on assigned Citrix systems related to administration, enhancements support, upgrades and issues. Anticipate and mitigate potential issues related to systems performance which may adversely impact users\' responsiveness within the systems. Research and recommend alternatives solutions regarding enhanced system performance. Provide technical expertise for system administration on the servers in the AgFirst environment ensuring optimal uptime and availability is achieved. Utilizing provided tool set; produce periodic reports on capacity and current usage of the Citrix systems. Review progress and evaluate results communicating with management on enhancement opportunities. Requirements: Bachelor\'s degree in technical subject or 3-5 years experience as administrator or technician of network systems, Microsoft Certified systems Engineer (MCSE) preferred, Proficient with Microsoft Exchange, Windows Server, TCP/IP addressing, Technical knowledge of Windows XP and 2003, Excellent oral and written communication skills. EEO','SC','',''),
('Senior Credit Reviewer/ Portfolio Analyst','14','This position is responsible for performing the asset validation of ACA\'s and OFI\'s funded by AgFirst, FCB; working with the Senior Credit Risk Officer to develop E-risk reports; and working with the Portfolio Risk Manager on portfolio management reporting. Responsibilities: Monitor the risk bearing ability of Associations and OFIs funded by AgFirst through the asset validation process including on-site or electronic loan reviews, and subsequent reports. Work with the Portfolio Risk Manager to develop and analyze reports related to the risk in the portfolio. Make portfolio presentations as requested. Work with the Senior Credit Risk Officer on generating E-risk reports and make presentations to the lending staff and management, related to Economic Capital.','','Requirements: Bachelor\'s Degree in Business, Accounting, Economics, or Finance; capable of effective verbal and written communications, minimum of 5 years experience in commercial lending or banking; proficient computer skills with experience in Microsoft Word and Excel, effective interpersonal and negotiation skills and ability to establish rapport with co-workers and customers, and willingness to travel 30% of the time. EEO','SC','',''),
('Lead Business Analyst','15','AgFirst is seeking an experienced Business Analyst to join its Business Process and Data Services department. ','Responsibilities: Development of new systems/applications such as Enterprise Data Warehouse, installation of purchased systems/applications such as Microsoft CRM and SharePoint, modification enhancements to existing systems/applications and development of methods and procedures. Translate high-level business requirements into detailed functional specifications.','Requirements: Four year degree in business, accounting or computer science or equivalent work experience. Minimum of 2 years of experience of successfully fulfilling the business data analyst role of software projects. Knowledge of banking operations or financial industry experience a plus. Knowledge of .NET, Web and Relational Database (SQL) technologies is a plus. EEO.','SC','',''),
('Legislative and Meeting Specialist Intern ','18','AgFirst is seeking a highly motivated intern for part time work this summer.  Blocks away from the University of South Carolina and free parking help make this internship one of the best in town.   ','Responsibilities-Assembling meeting material and packets; correspondence, nametags and badges, meeting database mailings and copying.  Additional administrative and clerical work will be assigned as needed.','Requirements- A student currently enrolled in classes or a recent college graduate.  Must be able to work 2030 hours a week.  A thorough working knowledge of Microsoft Excel and Word is necessary.  Must be detailed oriented and able to communicate effectively both orally and in writing.  Strong interpersonal skills a plus.  FAX resumes to 803-771-0752, AgFirst Farm Credit Bank, Attention: Recruiter,.  EEO. ','SC','AgFirst Farm Credit Bank, Attention: Recruiter, PO Box 1499, Columbia, SC 29202.','cmccroskey@agfirst.com'),
('Capital Markets Loan OperationsIntern','19','AgFirst is seeking a highly motivated accounting intern for part time work this summer.  Blocks away from the University of South Carolina and free parking help make this internship one of the best in town. ','Responsibilities:  Assists the Participation/Syndications Operations Department and other accounting areas in providingloan servicing and accounting services to the Bank and Associations. Responsible for completing special projects as directed by departmental management.  Prepares and enters information related to monthly/quarterly/annual reports and financial data. ','Requirements:  Must be a junior or senior currently enrolled in undergraduate or has already graduated in finance or accounting or a student in the masters program for accounting.  A thorough working knowledge of Microsoft office and complete proficiency in Excel is required.  Good communication skills both orally and written will be necessary.  Must be able to multi-task and work autonomously.  Ability to recognize and communicate errors and issues to appropriate staff members.  FAX resumes to 803-771-0752, AgFirst Farm Credit Bank, Attention: Recruiter','SC','AgFirst Farm Credit Bank, Attention: Recruiter, PO Box 1499, Columbia, SC 29202','cmccroskey@agfirst.com  '),
('Business Liaison','23','This position has responsibility for retaining and expanding company relationships and soliciting new mortgage business from prospective customers. Calls on existing or prospective customers within the framework of a business development call program. Develops leads, establishes priorities and prepares itineraries. Meets with customers or prospects to discuss their needs, outlines appropriate company services and resolves problems as necessary. Documents calls and results and makes reports to superiors as required. Assists in the implementation and coordination of business development call programs. Maintains close relations with appropriate company personnel. Discusses customer needs, problems or complaints. Keeps abreast of new products and services. Represents the company in various civic and community functions to further enhance its image and develop additional business. Works with product development personnel to review existing products and identifies opportunities for new products and services. Provides continuous training and advertisement to potential and existing customers  For immediate consideration, submit resume and cover letter stating salary requirements, to: Please no phone calls.  EOE  M/W/D/V.','','','SC','Human Resources, P.O. Box 1499, Columbia, S.C. 29202','cmccroskey@agfirst.com'),
('Administrative Assistant II','76','Performs varied administrative and secretarial duties for the Lending Department.  Exercises a high degree of knowledge, competence, and secretarial skill, and functions with considerable independence.  ','Responsible for coordinating the monthly board reports.  Responsible for contact with Dun & Bradstreet and the ordering of individual D&B reports.  Responsible for ordering supplies and maintaining the Lending Departments Operations Manual from information provided by the unit managers.  Communicates with various outside vendors; i.e., account representatives from Dun & Bradstreet, Forms & Supply, etc. Experience with Microsoft Suite, Access database. Must demonstrate the ability to learn new software quickly. Experience with Crystal Report and Business Objects a plus.','Requirements-  Four years of experience as an administrative assistant.  Ability to interact effectively with a diverse group of people.  Skill in operating word processing equipment; typing at 55 WPM.  Knowledge of grammar, spelling, punctuation, and required formats to recognize and correct correspondence and reports.  Excellent communication and human relation skills.  Knowledge of word-processing software, preferably WORD.  Ability to work independently with minimal instruction.  Reports to John Burnside.  Grade and Salary commensurate upon experience. EEO.','SC','',''),
('Relationship Manager ','A38','Apopka (Orlando) FL  (Farm Credit of Central Florida, ACA','Responsible for managing large complex commercial agribusiness relationships.  The successful candidate must have a proven track record in business development and a true understanding of managing lending relationships. Must possess outstanding interpersonal, communication, and organizational skills.  Should have a minimum of 3-5 years lending experience, be team-oriented and highly motivated.','Requires a B.S. in business, accounting; or economics. MBA a plus.  Grade and salary based on background and experience.  EEO','FL','Kathy MacNair, Human Resource Specialist, P.O. Box 8009, Lakeland, FL  33802-8009',''),
('CREDIT ANALYST','A39','','Successful candidate will be responsible for providing credit analysis on mid size, large and complex loans.  Analysis to be well documented to support credit decision and may be required to report findings to Loan Committee with recommendation.  Secondary responsibilities include ongoing industry trend and peer group analyses, portfolio analysis, and other special projects as assigned.','REQUIREMENTS:  Minimum of 4-year degree in agriculture/finance/business with an advanced degree preferred.  Good understanding of GAAP accounting.  Excellent written and oral communication skills.  Ability to effectively work with employees in a team environment to achieve business goals.  Capable of working independently and with little supervision.  Proficiency in use of Windows, Microsoft Word, Excel, and Moodys Financial Analyst.  Reports to the Chief Credit Officer.  Salary and grade dependent upon experience.  Fax 386-462-5040.   EOE.  Drug Free Workplace','FL','Farm Credit of North Florida, 12300 NW US Highway 441, Alachua, Florida  32615','cprice@fcnf.com'),
