('Loan Officer','A10','Dynamic, fast-growing lender seeks a qualified Loan Officer to work out of the Lewisburg branch office.  Primary market territory would be Columbia, Luzerne, Montour and Northumberland counties.   ','Responsibilities:  Business development with Part-time farms, rural home owners and rural property owners is an integral part of the position.','Requirements:  Applicant must be highly motivated and work independently to achieve branch and corporate goals.  Excellent sales and customer service skills.  Strong analysis, problem solving, communication and computer skills.  Residential lending experience, familiarity with FNMA and Freddie Mac originations a plus. Bachelors degree and/or equivalent experience in Sales, Business Administration, Economics, Finance, Agriculture or related field.  Excellent benefit package including:  Competitive base salary plus incentive.  Matched 401K & paid retirement plan.  Company car provided.  Send resume and desired salary confidentially or fax 717-796-9830.  Visit www.agchoice.com for more information or to apply online. Deadline for applications is January 31st.An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 900 Bent Creek Blvd., Mechanicsburg, PA 17050','patsmith@agchoice.com'),
('Financial Planner','A11','Searching for an exciting and fulfilling professional career dedicated to helping people realize their goals and dreams?  AgChoice Farm Credit, a leading provider of financial services to agribusiness and rural communities, is looking for the right professional to join our fast-growing wealth management team as an associate financial planner to help our wealth advisors provide a compelling experience for our clients.  This is an outstanding career opportunity for a future CFP candidate who possesses a great attitude and temperament for serving others.','Responsibilities: client service/administration.  financial plan preparation, reporting, technology support, research, investment and insurance sales, marketing support and various special projects.  Security and life insurance licenses are preferred but not required.  Excellent compensation and benefit package.  Office is located in West York with some regional travel required.  Send resume and desired salary confidentially. Visit www.agchoice.com for more information. An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 900 Bent Creek Blvd., Mechanicsburg, PA 17050 or fax 717-796-9830.','patsmith@agchoice.com '),
('Branch Manager','A23','AgChoice has an open position in Meadville Office. ','Responsibilities: Leads, trains, develops and motivatesbranch staff. Works with staff to achieve business growth objectives, profitability targets and meet asset quality standards.  Extends quality farm, farm related business and rural home loans through sound credit administration practices.  Monitor all personnel for adherence to policy, procedures and regulations.  Participate in business development activities to promote products and services.  Participate in public relations functions to enhance AgChoices community standing.','Requirements:  Education and/or experience equivalent to a Bachelor\'s degree in business, finance, accounting, agriculture or related field.  MBA or advanced education desirable.  Supervisory & managerial experience of 5+ years experience.  Farming background a plus.  Strong managerial, organizational, analytical, marketing and communication skills are essential.  Computer literacy a must.  Send resume and desired salary confidentially.  Visit www.agchoice.com for more information.  An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 900 Bent Creek Blvd., Mechanicsburg, PA 17050 or fax 717-796-9830','patsmith@agchoice.com'),
('Customer Service Specialist','A35','MidAtlantic Farm Credit, ACA, an established farm/rural home lender has a full-time position available immediately in Lancaster, PA. ','Position involves researching and answering customer service questions, reviewing daily reports, and general clerical duties. ','Successful candidate will possess a minimum of a high school education with specialized secretarial/administrative assistant training or equivalent experience. Must have excellent communication skills and be proficient with computer software applications.   Please send resume stating salary requirements.  We are a drug free work place.   Equal Opportunity Employer','PA','MidAtlantic Farm Credit, ACA P.O. Box 770 Westminster, MD  21158 Attention:  Human Resources Or fax resume to 410-848-2110','employment@mafc.com'),
('Loan Specialist','A36','MidAtlantic Farm Credit, ACA, an established farm/rural home lender has a full-time position available immediately in Lancaster, PA. ','Position involves preparing loan & legal documents and booking of loans. Answering phones, transferring calls and answering customers questions. ','Successful candidate will possess an AA degree in Accounting, Business, secretarial science or equivalent experience. Three years of loan processing or bookkeeping experience using general ledger and loan accounting systems.  Must have excellent communication skills and be proficient with computer software applications.   Please send resume stating salary requirements.  We are a drug free work place.  Equal Opportunity Employer','PA','MidAtlantic Farm Credit, ACA P.O. Box 770 Westminster, MD  21158 Attention:  Human Resources or fax resume to 410-848-2110','employment@mafc.com'),
('Mortgage Originator','A55','Business development is integral part of the position.  Our mortgage originators are highly motivated and work independently.  We are seeking mortgage originators who have residential lending experience and are familiar with FNMA and Freddie Mac originations.  Able to do business with Brokers.  Localized processing center. Great earnings potential! Excellent benefit package including: Competitive base salary plus incentive, Matched 401K, paid retirement plan, company car provided. Send resumes and desired salary confidentially.  An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','','','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 8900 Bent Creek Blvd, Mechanicsburg, PA 17050 or fax 717-796-9830','patsmith@agchoice.com'),
('LOAN PORTFOLIO MANAGER ','A 66','Dynamic, fast-growing lender seeks a qualified Loan Portfolio Manager for our Chambersburg location.   ','Our Loan Portfolio Managers are accountable as a resource person to a Lending Team for the development/servicing of loan packages.  Our Loan Portfolio Managers independently service loans and financial service accounts and maintain a working relationship with our customers.  Proficiency in development/analysis of loans on an independent basis.  Making sound credit decisions within delegated lending authority.  Accessing risk on existing accounts/portfolios.  Developing new business opportunities.','REQUIREMENTS:  Education and/or experience equivalent to a Bachelors degree in Business Administration, Agriculture, Economics or Finance.  Two years of financial/credit analysis or related agricultural lending experience preferred.  Strong analysis, judgment and oral or written communication skills.  Ability to be assertive and decisive in arriving at sound business decisions which serve the best interest of the association and borrower.  Excellent benefit package including  Competitive base salary plus incentive.  Matched 401K & paid retirement plan.  Send resume and desired salary confidentially.  Visit www.agchoice.com for more information or to apply online.   An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 900 Bent Creek Blvd., Mechanicsburg, PA 17050 or fax 717-796-9830','or patsmith@agchoice.com'),
('MORTGAGE LOAN ORIGINATOR','A68','As one of the Pennsylvanias leading rural residential lenders our Secondary Market Mortgage Division is continuing to grow and expand.  Presently we are seeking a full time mortgage loan originator forall Branch Banks. The opportunity for high income potential with a generous commission plan will be available.  In addition, a broad range of flexible mortgage solutions to serve almost any borrower will be provided. ','','Requirements:   Applicants must have knowledge of FNMA and Freddie Mac lending guidelines and have an established network of contacts that provide good quality mortgage referrals.  Preferred applicant should have at least 3+ years of recent experience in mortgage originations.  Excellent benefit package including:  Competitive base salary plus incentive  Matched 401K & paid retirement plan  Send resume and desired salary confidentially.  Visit www.agchoice.com for more information or to apply online. An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer M/F/V/H','PA','Pat Smith, AgChoice Farm Credit, 900 Bent Creek Blvd., Mechanicsburg, PA 17050 or fax 717-796-9830','patsmith@agchoice.com'),
('Loan Assistant','A22','AgSouth Farm Credit, ACA, an established agricultural lender, has an opening for a Loan Assistant in the Laurens, SC office. ','Duties include, but are not limited to, providing customer service and support to lending staff in loan accounting with an emphasis on customer accounts and document preparation. Applicants must possess strong communication, organizational, accounting, clerical, and computer skills. Salary is commensurate with experience. AA/EOE. Submit resumes','Requirements include an Associate Degree in a business related field or two years experience.','SC','Laurens Loan Assistant, PO Box 1146, Orangeburg, SC 29116','employment@agsouthfc.com'),
('MORTGAGE LOAN ORIGINATOR','48','AgSouth Farm Credit, ACA, a $1.5 billion rural lender, has an immediate opening for a Mortgage Originator in the Camden , SC office.  Successful candidate will represent AgSouth as an originator of home loans. ','Duties include marketing new clients, origination, documentation, analysis, disclosure, and interaction with borrowers. Commission Compensation plan with Health Benefits. AA/EOE.  Submit resume.  EOE','','SC','Camden Originator, AgSouth Farm Credit, PO Box 1146 , Orangeburg , SC 29116','employment@agsouthfc.com'),
('EXPERIENCED MORTGAGE ORIGINATOR','A60','to market and originate loans in the Sumter, S.C. and Florence, S.C. areas to be sold on the Secondary Mortgage Market. Commission based compensation plan eligible for health benefits.  EOE','','','SC','Human Resources, PO Box 13209, Florence, SC 29504','Arbor1@ArborOneACA.com'),
('Loan Officers','A27','We are currently seeking loan officers throughout our market territory  northern Virginia, the Shenandoah Valley, southwest Virginia & throughout West Virginia. Our loan officers are passionate about serving our borrowers with sound, productive solutions to their credit needs. An understanding of agriculture and ag-industries is always a plus!  We work in a unique team environment focused on exceeding our customers expectations.EEO','','Qualifications include an undergraduate degree in business, economics, finance, marketing or agriculture (or related studies) or a combination of comparable work experience/education. Exceptional communication skills and strong analytical / problem solving skills required. Must fully understand economic conditions in our markets and be able to effectively assess which borrowers are a good match for our products/services.','VA','','fcvrecruit@agfirst.com'),
('Loan Officer Trainee','A28','Colonial Farm Credit has an opening in their Mechanicsville office. ','Responsibilities: Serves present and prospective member customers with sound short-, intermediate-, and long-term credit according to association and district policies, standards and procedures. This position formulates business development strategies that target potential Farm Credit member customers, as well as referrals from builders, realtors, and other sources. Services all assigned existing loans within delegated authorities. Represents the association at local events and meetings. Promotes related services to all current and prospective member customers. ','Requirements: Education and/or experience equivalent to a BS or BA degree in Business Administration, Finance, Economics, or agricultural field. Strong interpersonal and sales skills. Agricultural background preferred.  Salary Grade 8 or 9 ($33,870 - $45,600) commensurate with experience and qualifications.  Send resumes.  The deadline is set for the close of business, Friday, April 4, 2008. EOE  M/F/D/V','VA','Sue Nicely, VP  Human Resources Colonial Farm Credit, ACA PO Box 727 Mechanicsville VA  23111 (804) 746-4581 (ext. 1120)  direct dial (804) 746-3159  fax','SNicely@ColonialFarmCredit.com'),
('Association President/CEO','','AgHeritage Farm Credit Services are accepting applications for its Little Rock Arkansas branch.  The Board of Directors of AgHeritage Farm Credit Services is seeking candidates for the position of President/CEO to lead the organization forward as the premier provider of financial services to agriculture and rural communities for the benefit of its member/owners.  This $600 million Farm Credit Association has over 50 employees in 9 branch locations dedicated to serving the agricultural credit and financial needs of more than 2400 stockholders in 24 central Arkansas counties.  AgHeritage FCS is part of the Farm Credit System; a nationwide agricultural financial services network providing  credit and related services to farmers, ranchers, rural homeowners, and agribusinesses throughout the United States.  The President/CEO provides leadership for long-range planning and directs the implementation of organizational plans and new programs. PLEASE EMAIL COVER LETTER AND RESUME TO. FINAL DATE FOR APPLICATION:  March 24, 2008.  ANTICIPATED INTERVIEW DATES:  Round 1:  April 10/11, 2008;  Round 2:  May 20, 2008.','Responsibilities: include the leadership, control, management and administration of all operations.  Duties also include developing and maintaining effective marketing and business development programs; developing and maintaining an effective and viable set of credit related financial services; developing an effective credit administration program; and maintaining a quality loan portfolio. In addition, the President/CEO is responsible for ensuring the financial viability of the organization and for developing and implementing plans and policies to enhance the competitive position of the organization within the lending marketplace.  He/she will identify strategic areas to support future development consistent with the association strategic and tactical objectives and will direct the development of a cohesive organization which is responsive to customer needs and efficient in its provision of credit and credit-related services.  The President/CEO represents the association and Farm Credit Services in various public relations responsibilities throughout the areas served and within the Farm Credit System.  The successful candidate must have highly developed interpersonal, communication and consultative management skills as well as demonstrated leadership abilities. The candidate should have broad financial experience in a major agricultural lending organization, including executive level managerial accountabilities and demonstrated abilities in working with boards of directors. ','Requirements: The position requires a Bachelors Degree in Finance, Business Administration, Agriculture, or closely related field and a minimum of ten years of leadership or management experience. The AgHeritage President/CEO position is a grade 23.','AK','Jay Lux Manager, Workforce Management Consulting Farm Credit Foundations: 375 Jackson St. St. Paul, MN 55101 Office phone:  651-282-8343 FAX:  651-282-8671','jay.lux@FarmCreditFoundations.com')";
